HEADWORD: Abbreviature
<hw>Ab*bre"vi*a*ture</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An abbreviation; an abbreviated state or form.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An abridgment; a compendium or abstract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is an excellent <qex>abbreviature</qex> of the whole duty of
a Christian.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abb wool</ent>⟦br⟧
